You are working on meridian-vscode — the VS Code extension wrapper for
Meridian, an AI architectural review agent.

## What this project is
- A thin VS Code extension (~300-400 lines total)
- It spawns the meridian-mcp Rust binary as a child process
- Communicates with it via MCP JSON-RPC over stdio
- Renders findings as inline editor decorations + Problems panel entries
- Has a webview sidebar panel for detailed finding display

## What this project is NOT
- It contains NO architectural analysis logic
- It makes NO direct calls to Claude or the Anthropic API
- It does NOT scan files itself — the Rust binary does that
- It does NOT call the Java backend directly

## File structure (keep it flat — this is intentionally thin)
- src/extension.ts     — activation, commands, save listener
- src/mcpClient.ts     — spawns binary, JSON-RPC comms
- src/decorations.ts   — inline editor decorations + diagnostics
- src/statusBar.ts     — status bar item
- src/findingsPanel.ts — webview findings sidebar

## VS Code API rules
- Always use ThemeColor for colors — never hardcode hex values
- Use vscode.DiagnosticCollection for Problems panel integration
- Decorations must be cleared before re-applying (avoid stacking)
- Webview HTML must escape all user content (use escHtml helper)
- Never use position: fixed in webview CSS (breaks iframe height)

## TypeScript rules for this project
- Strict mode on — no any, no non-null assertions without comment
- Dispose pattern: every disposable pushed to context.subscriptions
- Async errors must be caught — never let unhandled rejections surface
- Keep extension.ts as the only file that touches vscode.window directly

## MCP client rules
- Binary spawned once on activation, reused for all calls
- 30s timeout on all requests — Claude calls take time
- Stderr from binary goes to OutputChannel (not console.error in prod)
- Dispose kills the child process cleanly

## Testing
- Test with F5 in VS Code (Extension Development Host)
- Use a fixture project with known violations as the test workspace
- Check: decoration renders, Problems panel updates, status bar changes

